      "explanation": "Alternating Current AC current and voltage vary sinusoidally: V = V₀ sin(ωt), I = I₀ sin(ωt). Capacitor — Current leads voltage by 90°. The other options — 'Constant current', 'Current that only flows one way', and 'Direct current' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
