      "explanation": "AC Circuit Components Resistor : V and I are in phase. Alternating Current AC current and voltage vary sinusoidally: V = V₀ sin(ωt), I = I₀ sin(ωt). The other options — '90° out of phase', '180° out of phase', and '45° out of phase' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
