        {
          "text": "Capacitive reactance only",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Inductive reactance only",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Impedance Z = √(R² + (X_L − X_C)²) — total opposition to AC. Resonance — When X_L = X_C (ω = 1/√(LC)), impedance is minimum (Z = R) and current is maximum. The other options — 'DC resistance only', 'Capacitive reactance only', and 'Inductive reactance only' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
    },
    {
      "question_number": 6,
      "question_text": "At resonance in an RLC circuit:",
      "attempted": 2,
      "data_i18n": null,
      "options": [
        {
